<summary>
The <strong><c>&amp;lt;option&amp;gt;</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML">HTML</see> element is used to define an item contained in a <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/select">select</see>, an <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/optgroup">optgroup</see>, or a <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/datalist">datalist</see> element. As such, <c>&amp;lt;option&amp;gt;</c> can represent menu items in popups and other lists of items in an HTML document.
</summary>
